        <p style="font-size:var(--text-sm); color:var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom:var(--space-4);">You're preparing for Mains or doing Prelims + Mains together. You need analytical depth, answer writing practice, and essay frameworks.</p>

        <h4 style="color:var(--color-brand); margin-bottom:var(--space-2);">Your Action Plan:</h4>
        <ol style="font-size:var(--text-sm); margin-left:var(--space-5); margin-bottom:var(--space-4);">
          <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2);">Read <strong>Mains-level</strong> notes — analysis, dimensions, current affairs integration</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2);">Browse by <a href="/mains/">GS Paper</a> — GS1 through GS4 + Essay</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2);">Practice answer writing daily — use <a href="/mains-practice/">Mains prompts</a></li>
          <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2);">Read editorials on <a href="https://ujiyari.com/editorials/" target="_blank">Ujiyari.com</a> — essential for GS2/GS3 answers</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2);">Analyse Mains PYQs — understand what UPSC expects in 150/250 word answers</li>
        </ol>

        <div style="display:flex; gap:var(--space-3); flex-wrap:wrap;">
